  <li id="comment-33015" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/09399389348876533777" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Kathy</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/06/she-felt-like-cheering/#comment-33015"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-06-10T20:35:09-04:00">Sunday, June 10, 2012 at 8:35 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Oh goodness. I&#39;m so sorry for your loss. What a beautiful tribute. My mother would know just how you feel about your aunt; she had an aunt, her mother&#39;s sister, who was so much like a second mother to her that she called her Aunt Mom her entire life.</p>
<p>Pancreatic cancer is cruel. It seems to choose the gentlest, best-loved people: your aunt, my paternal grandmother. It&#39;s just not fair.</p>
    </div>

