    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Elizabeth RC</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/06/she-felt-like-cheering/#comment-32831"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-06-11T03:42:37-04:00">Monday, June 11, 2012 at 3:42 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My aunt is the same to me. In some ways closer than my mother, with whom I am very close. But my relationship with my aunt is not a friend, not a sister, nothing like my other aunts. No &#8211; very much like the love I share with my mother, but perhaps without the bittersweet part of growing and straining to find myself apart. Under the gaze of my aunt, I was always a true and whole woman, I just needed to grow into her. I am so sorry for your loss, and so glad that she gave you memories thick with sweetness so she is always closer than a mere memory.</p>
    </div>

