    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This post really hit home for me &#8230; Last year my mother died, May 29th a beloved pet of mine died of old age &#038; I also listened to Maurice Sendak&#39;s comments on Fresh Air many times. I lost my father when I was a very young child, so when my mother died the impact was very different &#038; really made me focus on my life.</p>
<p>I, like most, want to believe that we get to see all our loved ones again &#8230; After we die.  Beyond anything this is my hope about death. Reading your post is somehow comforting in that I&#39;m not alone in hope when dealing with loss. So thank you.</p>
<p>I followed you back when your header was this lush orange chocolate image &#8230; So imagine my happy surprise to read you will be a mom soon!  Congratulations.</p>
<p>Onward with life &#8230; And a new one!</p>
